	    <ThingDef ParentName="LightMechanoid">
      <defName>TW_Mech_Shellsplitter_Spider</defName>
      <label>Shellsplitter</label>
      <description>Short-range assault units spawned from Doxa-series incubation systems. Lightweight exoskeletons with high-frequency vibration materials enable rapid slashing attacks effective at infantry suppression and formation disruption.

Unlike most expendable mechanoids, Shellsplitter Spiders function as "engage-and-detonate" frontline disruptors. They deliver high-frequency melee strikes until structural failure triggers localized fragmentation explosions - damaging electronics while causing area-denial effects.

Typically deployed in swarms via rapid batch production, they execute infiltration, area denial, and tactical self-destruction missions with cold determination - fulfilling tactical purpose through approach, shred, and detonation.</description>
      <statBases>
        <MoveSpeed>6</MoveSpeed>
      </statBases>
    <tools>
      <li>
        <label>left blade</label>
        <labelNoLocation>blade</labelNoLocation>
        <capacities>
          <li>Cut</li>
          <li>Stab</li>
        </capacities>
        <power>20</power>
        <cooldownTime>2</cooldownTime>
        <linkedBodyPartsGroup>LeftBlade</linkedBodyPartsGroup>
        <alwaysTreatAsWeapon>true</alwaysTreatAsWeapon>
      </li>
      <li>
        <label>right blade</label>
        <labelNoLocation>blade</labelNoLocation>
        <capacities>
          <li>Cut</li>
          <li>Stab</li>
        </capacities>
        <power>20</power>
        <cooldownTime>2</cooldownTime>
        <linkedBodyPartsGroup>RightBlade</linkedBodyPartsGroup>
        <alwaysTreatAsWeapon>true</alwaysTreatAsWeapon>
      </li>
      <li>
        <label>head</label>
        <capacities>
          <li>Blunt</li>
        </capacities>
        <power>19</power>
        <cooldownTime>2</cooldownTime>
        <linkedBodyPartsGroup>HeadAttackTool</linkedBodyPartsGroup>
        <ensureLinkedBodyPartsGroupAlwaysUsable>true</ensureLinkedBodyPartsGroupAlwaysUsable>
        <chanceFactor>0.2</chanceFactor>
      </li>
    </tools>
      <race>
